cfg.h:
* Added: U32, HASH_OFFSET and HASH_PRIME

hash.c:
* Basic hash module. LexId calls these methods for interning. LexStr will do
	the same. We will write the intern table next.
* Added: functions: HashStart, HashU8, HashEnd. To be called in order.
* Added: enum HashTag.
	HashTag is a namespace for keys. All hashes encode the tag prior to the
	payload bytes. This lets us use the same table without
		id: hello
		and
		string: "hello"
	colliding. They co-exist as separate entries. The tag is used during
	hashing and for equality.

lexer.c:
* LexId: implemented hashing functions.